 Indentation - space, tab

 Indentation is the leading whitespace ( spaces and tabs ) before any statement in python.

Data types

Data types are the classification or categorization of data items.
Following are the standard or built-in data type of Python:

Numeric - int float ,complex
Sequence Type -string ,
list,
tuple - tuples cannot be modified after it is created. 

Boolean - Data type with one of the two built-in values, True or False. 

Set - Sets can be created by using the built-in set() function with an iterable object or a sequence by placing the sequence inside curly braces, separated by ‘comma’. 

Dictionary -Sets can be created by using the built-in set() function with an iterable object or a sequence by placing the sequence inside curly braces, separated by ‘comma’. 
       holds only single value as elements.


none -The None keyword is used to define a null variable or an object.

